::Divebomb::

"Ouch," notes Divebomb, as he spots the two missiles coming 
towards him in different directions. His eyes flicker between the 
missiles as they approach. He starts to fly backwards and lauches 
two bombs into the paths of the missiles, and detonates them, 
causing the missiles to blow up. "Whew..." He continues 
backwards, away from Element(G).


On 14 Apr 2001, at 17:53, Jen D. wrote:

> Three blasts hit Element but he barely noticed. A gestalt like him could 
> easily stand up to shots from small bots like Divebomb. He launched two more 
> missiles from his missile launchers, but this time he guided them to take 
> different paths. His mind stayed with them, ready to make them dodge if 
> Divebomb shot agian.
